message.content:
A rocket is a spacecraft that uses fuel to propel itself through the air or outer space. 

It is typically long and thin with cone-shaped or cylindrical sections. 

Rockets may come in different colors, but most are white or metallic in appearance. 

The surface is often smooth or slightly bumpy due to the various components that are attached to it. 

Rockets can be found in space, launching from launchpads on Earth, or on display in museums. 

They are essential for space exploration and have been used to study planets and explore the far reaches of the universe. 

Rockets have been used for various purposes for over a century, from military use to space travel.
